# Git workflow (solo developer)

The repo owner is the only developer. Keep git simple:

- **Always commit after editing project files** in a turn (the code/docs/rules
  you changed, plus any patch version bump). Do not leave those edits uncommitted
  or wait to be asked. This overrides generic “only commit when requested” guidance.
- **Commit directly to `main`.** Do not create feature branches, pull requests, or
  patch branches. Just change `main`.
- **Do not create git tags** unless the user explicitly asks.
- **Push to `origin main`** after that commit (same turn), unless the user said not
  to push.

This applies to all version bumps, fixes, and routine changes. Reserve heavier
flows (tags, store packaging) for when the user explicitly invokes them.

Do not sweep unrelated pre-existing dirty files into the commit unless the user
asked to ship/commit everything.
